description: Correction of FOMC statement, adding the omitted sentence "Longer-term inflation expectations remain well contained" (event highlighted by McMahon and Munday, 2022)
FOMC statement: The Federal Reserve is providing liquidity to facilitate the orderly functioning of financial markets
FOMC statement, Federal Reserve Board discount rate action
FOMC statement: Federal Reserve and other central banks announce specific measures designed to address liquidity pressures in funding markets

Federal Reserve announces it will initiate a program to purchase the direct obligations of housing-related government-sponsored enterprises and mortgage-backed securities backed by Fannie Mae, Freddie Mac, and Ginnie Mae. Federal Reserve announces the creation of the Term Asset-Backed Securities Loan Facility (TALF)
Statement Regarding Monetary Policy Implementation (addressed recent liquidity strains in the repo market by announcing Treasury bill purchases and repo operations to ensure ample reserves)
WSJ article: Bad Inflation Reports Raise Odds of Surprise 0.75-Percentage-Point Rate Rise This Week (event highlighted by Kurt Lunsford)
